Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.34,0:02:23.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.24,0:02:25.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Finally awake, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.21,0:02:29.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go and wash your face.\NThen we'll have breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.12,0:02:38.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After that, there's a place\Nthat we need to go today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.76,0:02:42.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, you need to learn how\Npeople in the town live.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.83,0:02:47.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to have this looked at,\Nso come with me to Ogi no Shimo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.67,0:02:53.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. So, where does one go\Nto have a spear serviced?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.64,0:02:55.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To a swordsmith.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.37,0:03:01.38,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 8\NThe Swordsmith
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.57,0:03:26.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea that there were this many\Nsmiths to be found in Kosenkyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.04,0:03:30.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's because Yogo steel\Nis famous in Rota, Sangal...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.77,0:03:35.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and even in my home\Ncountry of Kanbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.58,0:03:38.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you didn't know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.25,0:03:44.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have been taught that Yogo steel is a\Nvital trade commodity for our country...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.89,0:03:51.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but also that I should not view the\Nsteel actually being melted and worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.03,0:03:56.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, it's ancient\Ntradition among the Yogo aristocracy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.13,0:04:01.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that warriors who see a sword\Nbeing forged can never become powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.64,0:04:08.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you're on your way to see\Na blade being forged...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.58,0:04:11.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so I suppose you'll never\Nbecome powerful now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.88,0:04:15.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.42,0:04:18.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you never seen\Na sword being forged?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.62,0:04:22.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I was little,\NI've loved to watch steel...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.59,0:04:26.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that's been heated red-hot\Nand see sparks flying everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.06,0:04:28.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen it countless times by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.43,0:04:34.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then again, I'm neither\Nfrom Yogo nor an aristocrat...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.90,0:04:36.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so maybe it doesn't apply to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.75,0:04:47.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You still don't speak like a town child...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.58,0:04:50.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so sit and watch silently\Nonce we go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.15,0:04:50.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.50,0:05:09.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.24,0:05:16.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been away from Yogo for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.85,0:05:20.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As usual, I've been\Nliving dangerously...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:23.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but perhaps by the luck of the devil,\NI've managed to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.62,0:05:25.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.39,0:05:35.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I may get right down to business...\Nwould you mind taking a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:54.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like I will have\Nto forge you a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.52,0:06:00.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. In that case, I'd like to have\Nit made as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.99,0:06:08.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Before I start, there is a\Nquestion that I must ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.66,0:06:09.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.33,0:06:14.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard the rumors\Naround town, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.30,0:06:16.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,More or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.27,0:06:21.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to believe that\Nthese rumors could be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.88,0:06:27.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if you have indeed taken up\Narms against the court, then as a man...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.58,0:06:32.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who supplies the court with swords,\NI cannot ally myself with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:36.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you can explain your actions,\NI'd like to hear it before proceeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.26,0:06:43.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it is true that I have\Ntaken up arms against the court.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.20,0:06:49.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I must inform them\Nthat you are still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.81,0:06:52.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose that would be\Nthe right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.78,0:06:58.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do, now?\NStrike me down to silence me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.75,0:07:01.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you intend to report me,\NI'll have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.45,0:07:03.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But until I get you to forge\Na new spearhead for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.95,0:07:06.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm going to stay right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.99,0:07:10.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're putting me\Nin an awkward position.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.89,0:07:17.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm well aware how stubborn you are,\Nbut I'm even more stubborn than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.50,0:07:21.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do what you ask\Nuntil I know the full story.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.08,0:07:29.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who is the boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.68,0:07:35.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For various reasons,\Nhe's been left in my care.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.13,0:07:52.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.60,0:07:58.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what the town's\Ngossip mongers are saying about Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:07:59.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.38,0:08:03.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That she's a miscreant who will do\Nabsolutely anything for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.45,0:08:06.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're spreading rumors\Nthat the prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.45,0:08:11.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...actually died at the hands of\Na certain female bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.45,0:08:12.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How dare they!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.32,0:08:13.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa would never do such a...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.82,0:08:14.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa would never do such a...\NEnough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.99,0:08:46.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, I have other clients\Nscheduled to arrive soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.86,0:08:50.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to pick up their finished swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.10,0:08:55.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you insist on staying here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.77,0:08:59.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...would you at least do me the favor\Nof waiting in the other room?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.42,0:09:15.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will hear both sides of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.73,0:09:25.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.20,0:09:27.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.70,0:09:31.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.15,0:09:44.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are right on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.28,0:09:47.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we interrupted you\Nwhile you were working.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:56.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know that neither of you\Npay any heed to superstitions...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.09,0:09:58.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but I thought it would\Nbe good manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.59,0:10:00.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite all right.\NPlease, continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.23,0:10:06.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The recent manhunt must\Nhave been a difficult business.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.57,0:10:09.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.61,0:10:13.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The swords you left with me\Nwere notched quite badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.94,0:10:19.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. But we serve in the\Nimperial guard in the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.75,0:10:24.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I hear it, she was killed by the farmer\Nsoldiers who were scouring the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.72,0:10:28.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The wear and tear on those swords is\Ndue to constant use in training sessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.59,0:10:30.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.19,0:10:33.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from their condition,\Nthere would appear to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.03,0:10:36.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...skilled swordsmen in the guard\Nthat I am unaware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.27,0:10:42.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is for that reason that we requested\Nthat you forge new swords with edges...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.74,0:10:46.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...of jewel steel, which absorbs impact\Nbetter than normal steel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.44,0:10:50.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean to sound abrupt, but we\Nwould like to see the swords right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.85,0:10:53.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.12,0:10:57.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your swords are waiting\Nin that room over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.25,0:11:29.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.02,0:11:37.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.26,0:11:41.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Before you look at the swords...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.33,0:11:44.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there is something that\NI must ask the two of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.80,0:11:48.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?\NWhy the sudden formality?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.14,0:11:53.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What makes a Yogo sword so special?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.98,0:11:59.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you would know the answer\Nto that better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:07.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is my understanding that Yogo blades\Nare swords that are rarely seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.76,0:12:12.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that successfully merge two\Nnormally contradictory qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.33,0:12:15.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Suppleness that prevents breaking,\Nand sharpness of edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.77,0:12:22.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To go further, it is their shape,\Nheft, length, and curvature...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.37,0:12:25.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Each of these factors\Nhas been refined over 1,000 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.91,0:12:28.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and has already been perfected\Nfor their wielders.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.35,0:12:34.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all this time, we warriors\Nsee them as simply weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.32,0:12:38.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Both of your opinions\Nare perfectly reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.46,0:12:44.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is your opinion on the matter?\NWhat makes Yogo swords special?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.23,0:12:47.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here is what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.86,0:12:51.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other countries, swords are\Nthought of as nothing more...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.43,0:12:54.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...than tools meant to\Nwound or kill others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.00,0:13:00.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But in Yogo, our tradition is that\Ntheir creation and use are to be based...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.81,0:13:03.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...on a foundation of mutual trust\Nbetween warrior and blacksmith.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.85,0:13:08.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that in this relationship there is\Nthe potential to create an ultimate sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.92,0:13:10.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ultimate sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.45,0:13:11.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.69,0:13:17.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Every sword you forge is praised\Nas a masterpiece among masterpieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.26,0:13:20.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Masterpieces? Far from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.76,0:13:23.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They say that when someone\Ngrips the hilt of a sword I've made...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.47,0:13:27.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...he is suddenly consumed by\Nthe urge to kill someone with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.37,0:13:29.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So they are no more than\Ninstruments of calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.91,0:13:33.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But a sword that kills no one,\Nsevering only the bonds of karma...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.94,0:13:37.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is what I consider\Nto be the ultimate sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.41,0:13:43.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To forge such a sword one day...\NThat thought is always on my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.59,0:13:49.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, it is no easy task.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.96,0:13:53.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A great sword is achieved when\Nboth warrior and blacksmith...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.43,0:13:57.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...have reached the\Npinnacle of their craft.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.83,0:14:00.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When that balance has broken down...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.74,0:14:04.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that is when a so-called\Ncursed sword is born.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.11,0:14:10.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is for that reason that I am selective\Nabout whom I forge a sword for.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.21,0:14:12.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, that I must be selective.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.42,0:14:20.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps, but how many warriors\Nare there in this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.26,0:14:23.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that might inspire you\Nto forge such a sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.93,0:14:31.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me think... In all my years,\Nthere has been exactly one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.20,0:14:35.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only one that I felt may have\Nachieved the pinnacle of his craft.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.41,0:14:40.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are saying that this warrior\Nmet your standards?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.98,0:14:46.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I used all of the skill that I had\Nat my disposal at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.68,0:14:48.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to forge a sword for this person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.65,0:14:50.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What sort of man was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.59,0:14:55.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a fellow student of the sword arts,\Nyou have piqued my curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.19,0:14:57.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will you tell us about this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.56,0:15:01.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was 24 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.13,0:15:06.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This person was a warrior\Nof a distant land...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.00,0:15:09.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...constantly on the road,\Ntraveling from country to country.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.31,0:15:16.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His mastery of his weapon was such\Nthat I had never before witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.75,0:15:20.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And although completely at odds with\Nhis appearance, there was a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.45,0:15:23.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who was constantly\Nat this warrior's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.09,0:15:28.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A child?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.96,0:15:34.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, a friend who had fallen\Nvictim to some sort of palace intrigue...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.70,0:15:36.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...had entrusted his child to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.07,0:15:42.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was because of this that the warrior\Nwas driven out of his home country.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.91,0:15:45.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Immediately afterwards...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.87,0:15:50.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...several assassins were\Ndispatched to kill the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.78,0:15:55.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so he came to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.72,0:16:00.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...saying that he wanted me to forge\Nhim a sword to fight these assassins.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:03.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I turned him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.23,0:16:06.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I said that I had no interest in forging\Na sword for some foreigner...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.60,0:16:08.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who didn't know the first thing\Nabout Yogo swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.76,0:16:11.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But then, something made you\Nchange your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.87,0:16:16.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He told me of the assassins\Nwho were sent to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.34,0:16:18.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Told me what sort of men they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.71,0:16:21.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When he told me this story,\Nmy heart was moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.08,0:16:26.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They gathered the land's bravest fighters\Nand sent the most skilled assassins?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.52,0:16:29.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No... Although indeed\Nthey were the bravest...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.52,0:16:32.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the men sent to kill him were\Nall dear friends of the warrior...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.82,0:16:35.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...people with whom he had shared\Nboth sadness and joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.23,0:16:40.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As he kept the child safe...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.76,0:16:43.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the warrior was forced to slay\Nhis former best friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.87,0:16:46.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...one by one with his own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.24,0:16:50.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The man who sent the assassins\Nmust have thought a great deal...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.67,0:16:55.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...about what would cause\Nthe warrior the most suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:59.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the assassins had just as little\Ndesire to hunt down the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.28,0:17:05.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But each of their families\Nwas being held hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.29,0:17:08.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so, left with no choice,\Nthey came to kill the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.79,0:17:10.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a despicable act...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.06,0:17:13.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard his story,\Nthis is the thought that struck me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.90,0:17:17.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That I wanted to forge the\Nultimate sword for this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.60,0:17:21.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted him to cut himself\Nfree of his cruel fate...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.24,0:17:23.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To sever the bonds of karma...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:27.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so I forged him a sword,\Nsuffused with special passion...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.78,0:17:33.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, was this warrior able to free himself\Nfrom the fate he was burdened with?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.92,0:17:41.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looking back on it now, my skills\Nhad yet to fully mature at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:47.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, he cut down each of the men\Nwho had once been his dearest friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.63,0:17:49.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Using the sword that\NI had forged for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.04,0:17:56.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What of the warrior?\NWhere is he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.64,0:17:59.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He is no longer among the living.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.51,0:18:05.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even on his deathbed, the actions that\Nhe took continued to break his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.15,0:18:08.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what about the child?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.85,0:18:12.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He raised her with care until\Nshe reached adulthood...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.85,0:18:15.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and she is alive and well to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.19,0:18:16.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.79,0:18:23.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But why would the warrior go to\Nsuch lengths to protect the child?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.97,0:18:28.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The warrior would be signing\Nhis own death warrant...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.04,0:18:31.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...by fleeing the country\Nwith the child in tow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.94,0:18:36.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And even if she was the child of a friend,\Nshe was no relation to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.31,0:18:40.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't the warrior have simply\Nrefused his friend's request?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.58,0:18:44.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that certainly is a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.95,0:18:48.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly strikes me as odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:54.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth, by some\Ncoincidence I know of someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.53,0:18:57.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who reminds me\Na great deal of that warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.73,0:19:02.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This person also fled from pursuers\Nafter being suddenly entrusted...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.37,0:19:05.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...with the child of a\Ntotal stranger one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.01,0:19:09.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And when the child had been\Ntaken from her at one point...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.41,0:19:14.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...she took him back, putting her\Nown life at risk in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.48,0:19:20.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what is most surprising is that\Nshe didn't kill a single one...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.96,0:19:25.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...of the many pursuers who\Nwere trying to take her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.99,0:19:30.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As for what made this person agree\Nto take the child of another into her care...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.10,0:19:33.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I cannot even begin to\Nguess at her motivations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.50,0:19:38.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it was just because she\Ndidn't have it in her to turn a blind eye...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.14,0:19:41.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to a helpless life that was\Nabout to flicker and die in front of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.58,0:19:48.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For that reason, she employed masterful\Ntechniques that would not prove lethal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.58,0:19:52.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is a most fascinating story.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.52,0:19:55.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Out of curiosity,\Nwhat became of this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:02.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It pains me to say it,\Nbut she left this world some days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.93,0:20:07.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.17,0:20:11.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I listened to your story just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.11,0:20:15.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it occured to me that perhaps this\Nwarrior might have been worthy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:19.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...of wielding your ultimate blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.35,0:20:22.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me for subjecting you\Nto such idle talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.78,0:20:28.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. It is I who have\Ndetained you for far too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.79,0:21:09.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will take our leave now. You have\Ndone us a great service once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.57,0:21:20.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was there another customer here\Nbefore us, by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.14,0:21:22.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.48,0:21:26.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you mean that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.32,0:21:29.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a spear was left here with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.25,0:21:32.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised that a smith\Nof your caliber...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.19,0:21:34.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...would stoop to working on\Na weapon as lowly as a spear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.79,0:21:39.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I work on whatever strikes\Nmy fancy, even spears.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.63,0:21:43.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of that I have no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.70,0:21:44.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:07.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For a moment there, I thought that\Nmy luck had finally run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.96,0:22:12.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please feel free to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.26,0:22:18.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have heard both sides\Nof the story now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.13,0:22:22.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come again in seven days.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.18,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.54,0:24:45.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Feelings of Chagum's loved ones...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.01,0:24:48.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...drive a certain young star reader\Nto take action.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.68,0:24:52.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Shuga Thirsts."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 9\NShuga Thirsts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.65,0:24:56.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A fallen one will arrive at an answer.
